The Chronicle Nduduzo Tshuma, Political Editor President Emmerson Mnangagwa this morning commissioned 76 Zupco buses at a colourful ceremony held at the City Hall parking lot in Bulawayo. The President said most of the buses will service rural provinces of Matabeleland North and Matabeleland South and the remainder to service Bulawayo. <img class="alignnone wp-image-474512 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/11/zupco33.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/11/zupco33.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/11/zupco33-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> He said the Government decided to recapacitate Zupco to provide affordable transport to the people and protect them from unscrupulous players who were charging prohibitive fares. More to followâ€¦